{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01XLv3DLAP516fdZi96NpLVp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, `apierrors` is available. Now I have everything I need to write the implementation.\n\nHere is the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## File to modify\n\n**`internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go`**\n\nThe full updated file:\n\n```go\npackage podplacement\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\timgspecv1 \"github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/specs-go/v1\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/image/fake/registry\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Internal/Controller/PodPlacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook\", func() {\n\tWhen(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", func() {\n\t\tContext(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should ignore pods with a non-empty nodeName\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"test-namespace\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeName(\"test-node-name\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t\tContext(\"when a pod is created in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not add the scheduling gate even when namespaceSelector matches all namespaces\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tns := &corev1.Namespace{\n\t\t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"openshift-kube-apiserver\"},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif err := k8sClient.Create(ctx, ns); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tExpect(apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err)).To(BeTrue(),\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"unexpected error creating namespace: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-apiserver-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(\n\t\t\t\t\tcorev1.PodSchedulingGate{Name: utils.SchedulingGateName},\n\t\t\t\t), \"scheduling gate should not be added to control-plane pods in openshift-kube-apiserver\")\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n## What changed\n\nThree things were added to the existing file:\n\n1. **New imports**: `corev1`, `apierrors`, `metav1`, and `utils` — needed for the namespace creation, pod scheduling gate assertion, and the control-plane node selector constant.\n\n2. **New `Context` block** (after the existing `Context(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", ...)` block, still inside the `When` block): `Context(\"when a pod is created in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", ...)`.\n\n3. **The `It` block** inside that Context:\n   - Creates the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace (idempotently, tolerating `AlreadyExists`).\n   - Builds a pod using the fluent builder with `WithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\")` — this sets `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` as a node selector, which is what real kube-apiserver pods have.\n   - Creates the pod via `k8sClient.Create`, which routes through the webhook.\n   - Asserts that the scheduling gate `multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate` is **not** present on the pod.\n\n## Why the pod is excluded\n\nThe webhook's `shouldIgnorePod` (`pod_model.go:437`) returns `true` when `pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` is true. `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector` (`pkg/models/pod.go:134`) checks for `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` or `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` in `pod.Spec.NodeSelector`. Since the test pod has the control-plane selector, the webhook skips adding the scheduling gate — even though the CPPC's `NamespaceSelector` is nil (meaning \"all namespaces are in scope\").\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# Run just this test\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='openshift-kube-apiserver'\" make unit\n\n# Or run all webhook tests\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook'\" make unit\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5726,"cache_read_input_tokens":76724,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5726,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"012c9df5-6571-43ba-8518-84ca4932300f","uuid":"9688247e-5ad0-480c-acca-aa85667bd928","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:51:50.642Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDjY4qQq15obRrQgxcD8"}
